# Rust
/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock.bak

# Frontend
/web/node_modules/
/web/dist/
/web/.vite/
/web/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
*.log

# Live2D model assets (large binaries; users supply their own).
# The Live2D Cubism SDK sample models (Haru, Hiyori, Mark, etc.) ship
# from Live2D under a free-for-individuals license and shouldn't be
# redistributed via this repo. Bring them under web/public/live2d/.
/web/public/live2d/
/web/public/live2dcubismcore.min.js

# Local config (per-machine, may contain secrets / character roster)
companion.toml
companion.runtime.json
companion.characters.json
.env
.env.*

# Runtime SQLite database for Pulse — generated on first start
/data/
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# E2E test artifacts (saved audio, captured frames)
/e2e_audio.wav
/e2e_*.wav
# Local CDP screenshots / scratch files saved during debugging.
# Underscore prefix is the convention we use for "test scratch" so
# they're trivial to ignore without touching this file each round.
scripts/_*

# Editor / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local AI assistant config
CLAUDE.md
.claude/

# Tauri binaries (the sidecar is staged from target/release per build,
# don't commit a stale copy). Real icons can stay tracked.
/apps/companion-tauri/binaries/

# Python bytecode (anywhere)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Per-machine artifacts under tools/ — voice clones are user-supplied,
# audio outputs are scratch from manual testing.
tools/avatar/cloned_voices/

# Test-rig outputs (audio samples, screenshots, logs). The rigs
# themselves (tts_tools/) are tracked; their outputs in tts_samples/
# are scratch only.
/tts_samples/

# Working / progress scratch docs — keep notes locally, not in git.
POLISH_PROGRESS.md
